The article is a letter from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Speaker of the House, requesting Congress to consider budget amendments for various departments and agencies. The proposed amendments aim to reflect the policies assumed in the Fiscal Year (FY) 2023 Budget. The letter includes amendments for the Departments of Agriculture, Defense, Health and Human Services, the Interior, Justice, Labor, and Transportation, as well as the Commission of Fine Arts.

The amendments would increase the overall discretionary budget authority in the FY 2023 Budget by $85 million. Additionally, an amendment is provided for the Department of Energy's Defense Environmental Cleanup account, seeking to increase funding by $191 million for specific cleanup efforts.

Furthermore, an amendment is proposed to increase the authorization of appropriations for the Las Vegas Wash wetlands restoration and Lake Mead improvement project, as provided by the Water Resources Development Act of 2000.

The letter also contains eight FY 2023 Budget amendments for the Legislative Branch, which are transmitted without change as a matter of comity and tradition. These amendments would increase the overall discretionary budget authority in the FY 2023 Budget by $2 million.

Overall, if all the proposed amendments are considered, they would increase the overall discretionary budget authority in the FY 2023 Budget by $278 million. The details of the proposal can be found in the enclosed letter from the Director of the Office of Management and Budget.